<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Melescanu Departs for Denmark, Finland </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Melescanu Departs for Denmark, Finland </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306181994 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1625 GMT 13 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1306181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 13/6/1994 -- Romanian Minister 
of Foreign Affairs Teodor Melescanu is going to visit Denmark 
and Finland in order to analyze the stage of Romania's relations 
with the two countries, with a special stress on the economic 
issues. 
  Before leaving for Denmark, the Romanian foreign minister 
said his visit in the two northern countries was an "obligatory 
leg" in a process of opening the bilateral relations, 
considering also the fact that Denmark and Finland are both 
members of the European Union. The Romanian chief diplomat 
referred in his statement to Romania's interest in matters 
concerning agriculture, food industry, and environment 
protection, economic fields in which the two countries are very 
advanced. 
  "It is a first good-will mission within an official visit 
aiming to review the things that we have accomplished together 
-- rather few so far -- especially in the economic field," said 
Minister Melescanu. 
  The Romanian foreign minister is paying an official two-day 
visit in Denmark on June 14-15, at the invitation of his 
counterpart, Niels Helveg Petersen. On June 16-17, the Romanian 
chief diplomat will be visiting Finland at Mr. Heikki Haavisto's 
invitation. Minister Teodor Melescanu is scheduled also to 
attend the Crans Montana forum in Switzerland, on June 17-18. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

