<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kovac Ill; U.S. Visit `Will Take Place' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kovac Ill; U.S. Visit `Will Take Place' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406182394 Prague CTK in English 1724 GMT 14 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1406182394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, June 14 (CTK) -- As President Michal 
Kovac has caught flu, he has canceled some events planned for 
this week, presidential spokeswoman Anna Turenicova told CTK 
today. Kovac was scheduled to visit East Slovakia and open a 
branch of the Presidential Office in Kosice, East Slovakia. As 
the illness is not serious, "his visit to the United States, 
planned for next week, will take place," Turenicova added. 
  Along with his Hungarian counterpart Arpad Goncz, Kovac will 
be presented the prestigious award of the Institute for 
East-West Security Studies (IEWSS) on June 22 in New York. They 
have been conferred the award for their remarkable contribution 
to international cooperation and understanding between the two 
countries' nations and effort to settle ethnic problems. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

