<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moravcik Sees Austrian EU Vote as `Positive' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik Sees Austrian EU Vote as `Positive' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506184794 Prague CTK in English 1415 GMT 15 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1506184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, June 15 (CTK) -- Slovak Premier Jozef 
Moravcik hailed the results of Sunday's [12 June] referendum in 
which Austria voted for European Union (EU) membership as "very 
positive" today. 
  "What happened in Austria can help us succeed in our efforts 
to join the EU," he told CTK. 
  The vote was also welcomed by the Slovak Foreign Ministry, 
which issued a statement saying that Austria's path was "in many 
ways a source of experience for Slovak foreign policy, whose 
strategic aim is full EU membership." It also expressed interest 
in intensifying Slovak-Austrian relations as a "prototype for 
Slovakia's relations in an integrated Europe." 
  By voting to join, Austria had assumed not only the right to 
take part in joint decision making in the EU but also the 
responsibility of deepening European integration, the ministry 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

