<H3> <TI>   Serbs `Maltreat' Albanians Crossing Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs `Maltreat' Albanians Crossing Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406183694 Tirana ATA in English 1024 GMT 14 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1406183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 14 (ATA) -- People have to wait in long 
queues up to seven hours to cross the border points between 
Kosova and Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM] in Han Elezi and Gllobocica. 
  Serbian forces in this border crossing point exercise a 
severe and detailed control, maltreat and provoke Albanians, get 
their passports under various pretexts, especially as a 
punishment for visits to Albania. 
  After being deprived of their passports, the Albanians are 
sent to jail or punished by very high fines. 

</TEXT>

