<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Organized Terror' by Serbs on Albanian Education </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Organized Terror' by Serbs on Albanian Education </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406183794 Tirana ATA in English 1021 GMT 14 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1406183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, June 14 (ATA) -- During the last years 
48,000 pupils and 1,200 teachers have been forced to abandon 
their schools and homes in Kosova to escape Serb police 
persecutions. 
  According to reports by the "Naim Frasheri" Albanian 
Teachers' League, during this period, Serbian police have beaten 
and maltreated more than 3,250 teachers, 300 pupils, and a 
considerable number of parents who have not agreed to give up 
Albanian school. The police have killed seven teachers and 
parents. 
  "This organised terror against Albanian education continues 
to escalate, and recently, tens of schoolmasters and directors 
of education institutions have been arrested and kept in jail," 
ATA reporter informs from Prishtina. 

</TEXT>

