<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rally, Government-Union Talks Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rally, Government-Union Talks Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606151694 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1300 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1606151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The negotiations that were interrupted at 0130 
between the government team, which includes State Ministers Dan 
Mircea Popescu and Florin Georgescu, Viorel Hrebenciuc, general 
secretary of the government, and Octavian Partenie, head of the 
office in charge of the government's relations with trade unions 
and employers organization, and counselors, experts, and 
representatives of the Alfa Cartel and the National Trade Union 
Block and delegations led by Alfa Cartel Bogdan Hossu, resumed 
shortly before 1500. 
  In the first 15 minutes, the representatives of trade unions 
explained that the minutes of the meeting, which were completed 
last night but not signed, include the government's viewpoint 
but, as far as the viewpoint of trade unions are concerned, 
there are several controversial points. Romulus Nita, vice 
president of the Alfa Cartel, immediately insisted that the 
talks should focus on Government Ordinance Number 13 to find 
ways to invalidate it. At this hour, the talks are in progress, 
our correspondents informed us. 
  Meantime, our correspondent informed us on the phone that 
Victoria Square continues to be occupied by Alfa Cartel trade 
union members. Trade union representatives from Focsani and 
Tulcea have joined the groups of demonstrators. The size of the 
law enforcement units, as well as their technical equipment, 
have also increased considerably. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

