<H3> <TI>   Unions Issues Communiques </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unions Issues Communiques </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606182994 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1700 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1606182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A communique released by the Alfa Cartel [Trade 
Union Confederation] says, quote, the government continues to 
spread misleading information. The protesters did not resort to 
violence, did not even get close to the sidewalk [in Victory 
Square], but the authorities continue to incite, unquote. The 
communique requests support from all state institutions to adopt 
a positive stance as soon as possible to avoid possible 
regrettable violence. 
  Another communique released by the National Trade Union 
Bloc, 
in its capacity as a participant in the rally organized by Alfa 
Cartel, informs public opinion about, quote, the constant and 
arrogant refusal of the executive to solve the problems of the 
trade unions and, at the same time, the obviously hypocritical 
way in which dialogue is being mimed, unquote. 

</TEXT>

