<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Responds to Turkish Overflight Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Responds to Turkish Overflight Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606173394 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1606173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Ministry Spokesman Radko Vlaykov replied to 
a question from BTA regarding reports in certain mass media in 
Turkey, according to which part of the Turkish contingent of 
Blue Helmets is supposed to be transported to Bosnia-Herzegovina 
on civil aircraft flying over Bulgarian territory. 
  In his reply, the Bulgarian Foreign Ministry spokesman 
stated 
that this issue has not been officially raised with Bulgaria. 
He said that all our neighbors have been repeatedly informed of 
the Bulgarian position regarding the conflict in former 
Yugoslavia. He recalled some of the elements of this position: 
nonparticipation in the conflict, whether directly or 
indirectly, including under the aegis of the United Nations, and 
appeals made to neighboring Balkan states to refrain from 
participation in the conflict. He said that a nationwide 
consensus exists in Bulgaria on this issue, which is shared by 
the political forces, the president, parliament, and the 
government, and no grounds exist for altering this position. 

</TEXT>

