<F P=106> [Statement by Prime Minister Aleksander Meksi at Rinas </F>
Airport on 15 June -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Announcer] Prime Minister Meksi left for 
Switzerland. 
  [Correspondent] Heading a government delegation, Prime 
Minister Aleksander Meksi left for Switzerland today to attend 
the Crans Montana forum proceedings. High-level officials from 
various countries of the world have been invited to this 
meeting. The Crans Montana forum representatives organize 
roundtable talks to discuss situations and prospects of the 
development of world cooperation. 
  Before departure, Mr. Meksi made this statement for the 
television: 
  [Begin Meksi recording] Our delegation that will participate 
in the annual meeting of the Crans Montana Forum aims to present 
the Albanian reform with its results and difficulties, the 
institutional changes carried out in Albania, their perspective 
and future goals. It also intends to profit from the experiences 
of other countries that entered into reform before us or at the 
same time as us. As is known, this annual meeting of the forum 
will be attended by delegations from all former-communist 
Eastern European countries, as well as countries from Central 
Europe and international structures. That is, we will have an 
exchange of experiences and opinions, as well as contacts that 
will benefit Albanian foreign policy and be in the interests of 
Albania's economic development. 
  I think that these meetings are useful. Our delegation will 
try to truly present the political, economic, and institutional 
reforms in Albania, with all their benefits and difficulties. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

