  [Text] Gabor Nahlik, deputy chairman of Hungarian 
Television, following yesterday's six-party discussions about 
the future of Hungarian radio and television, today issued the 
following statement: 
  In response to the 15 June announcement by Prime Minister 
Peter Boross, I am glad that the appointment and relief of the 
leaders of Hungarian Television will be the result of a 
six-party agreement. I consider it natural that the next leader 
of Hungarian Television should take over after a thorough 
economic and legal examination. I am at the disposal of any of 
the examining organizations. 
  Budapest, 16 June 1994 
  Signed: Dr. Gabor Nahlik, deputy chairman of Hungarian 
Television 

