<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Businessman Founds Political Movement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Businessman Founds Political Movement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606175394 Bratislava SME in Slovak 15 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU1606175394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SME </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(asa)"] </F>
  [Text] Businessman Rudolf Mosny is putting himself forward 
in the new role of politician and is entering onto the Slovak 
political scene. Yesterday, he briefed correspondents on his 
new political movement, New Slovakia [Nove Slovensko] 
(established on 6 May 1994), whose aim is to reverse the 
unfavorable development and to renew the citizen's faith in the 
legislative and executive bodies. The New Slovakia movement 
acknowledges the basic principles of modern liberalism, founded 
on the inviolability of democratic values, and affirms an 
effective market economy that provides social guarantees. The 
movement will join the preelection campaign and is counting on 
getting into parliament. So far, it is represented in about 
half of the districts in the Slovak Republic. 

</TEXT>

