<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karadzic Briefs Milosevic on Talks in Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karadzic Briefs Milosevic on Talks in Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606121294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1134 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 16 Jun (TANJUG) -- Slobodan Milosevic, 
president of the Republic of Serbia, today received Radovan 
Karadzic, president of the Srpska republic, following the 
latter's return from Moscow. He briefed Milosevic on his talks 
with Russia's top representatives, particularly with Russia's 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, regarding the peace process in 
former Bosnia- Herzegovina and efforts to advance it 
successfully, the office of the Serbian president has announced. 
  Peace is undoubtedly the highest interest so the Serb side 
will contribute as much as possible to a political solution to 
the crisis, the statement says. 
  As stated, satisfaction was expressed with Russia's unbiased 
attitude and its efforts to help negotiations between the 
warring sides in Bosnia-Herzegovina as well as with expectations 
that the international community secure equal treatment for 
every participant in this process. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

