<H3> <TI>   Negotiations With Serbian Krajina Canceled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Negotiations With Serbian Krajina Canceled </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Croat Reporters Denied Access </H4>

<F P=102> LD1606134694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1300 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have just learned that the negotiations between 
representatives of the Croatian authorities and the Serbs from 
the protected zones have been canceled due to the Serbs' refusal 
to allow representatives of Croatia's media to attend the talks. 
This is what international mediator Kai Aide said at a news 
conference which ended a few minutes ago at the UN Protection 
Forces headquarters in Zagreb. The international mediators will 
try to reach agreement on another date for these negotiations. 

</TEXT>

