<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Latvia Urged To Revise Citizenship Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Latvia Urged To Revise Citizenship Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606084794 Prague CTK in English 1901 GMT 15 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1606084794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, June 15 (CTK) -- At their current session 
in Prague, the Committee of High Commissioners of the Conference 
on Security and Cooperation in Europe (CSCE) today urged Latvia 
to re-evaluate its law on state citizenship adopted last week. 
The CSCE was asked to take a stance on the issue by the Russian 
Foreign Ministry. 
  The law, which sets hard conditions for acquiring Latvian 
citizenship, is a thorn in the flesh of the strong Russian 
minority living in the country. CSCE spokesman told journalists 
that the Latvian delegate to the Prague session, Ivars Pundurs, 
did not rule out that his government would make certain changes 
in the law. CSCE commissioners accepted this stance with 
satisfaction, the spokesman said. 

</TEXT>

