<H3> <TI>   Ministry Cites Agriculture Talks With FYROM </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Cites Agriculture Talks With FYROM </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506193194 Tirana ATA in English 1015 GMT 15 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1506193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Press Release of the Ministry of Agriculture and Food in </F>
Regard to its Delegation Visit in The Former Yugoslav Republic 
of Macedonia" -- ATA headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, June 15 (ATA) -- The Ministry of 
Agriculture and Food reported through a press release that the 
talks between the Albanian and Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] Ministry of Agriculture 
delegations were characterized by a spirit of understanding and 
respect of the mutual interests. 
  The two sides agreed on all the questions they discussed 
concerning the problems of the mutual interest. The Albanian 
party insisted that the documents to be signed should refer to 
Macedonia with the name that the United Nations has given to 
this republic since Albania too has recognized its eastern 
neighbour by this name. The press release said that there was 
no personal approach on this question. 
  The minister of agriculture and food, Hasan Halili, who 
headed the delegation, clarified that the stand of the 
delegation was in conformity with that of the Albanian 
Government on this issue. The press release informs the public 
that issues about which the two delegations talked will be 
reflected in a protocol which is expected to be signed soon. 

</TEXT>

