<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   1,562 Families Resettled in Durres District </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1,562 Families Resettled in Durres District </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506193494 Tirana ATA in English 1022 GMT 15 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1506193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Durres, June 15 (ATA) -- Some 1,562 families from 
other districts, consisting of 9,419 members, have been settled 
in Durres district during the past three months, according to a 
report by the Ministry of Agriculture and Food. The great 
"rush" of people, some 465 families, have been settled in the 
Jub Sukth commune. 
  Most of the families come from the northern east of Albania 
but there are also families from southern east, central and 
western Albania. They are mainly from Pogradec, Korce, and 
Tirana. The families from northeastern Albania, which fled from 
the terrain dangers, have been given 176 hectares of land 
according to a decision by the government. 

</TEXT>

