<H3> <TI>   Guards Stop Trucks Smuggling Gasoline to FRY </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guards Stop Trucks Smuggling Gasoline to FRY </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406201794 Sofia BTA in English 1804 GMT 14 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1406201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, June 14 (BTA) -- Bulgarian border guards 
intercepted an attempt to smuggle three trucks loaded with 
petrol across the Bulgarian-Yugoslav border at 10 AM today. The 
trucks refused to obey the border guards who were forced to use 
their guns. An unidentified person was wounded 25 m from the 
border on Bulgarian territory, his life being out of danger. He 
was rendered medical aid. 
  An extraordinary meeting with Yugoslav border authorities is 
being held on the site of the incident to clarify all 
circumstances. Experts of the regional directorate of the 
interior in the town of Montana have been sent to the site of 
the incident, the Press Office of the Interior Ministry reported. 

</TEXT>

