<H3> <TI>   Communist Party Leader Cited on Benes Decrees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Communist Party Leader Cited on Benes Decrees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606195094 Prague CTK in English 1711 GMT 16 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1606195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Prague, June 16 (CTK) -- Attacks against the 
post-war decrees issued by President Edvard Benes and a campaign 
conducted against the completion of the Lidice monument were 
linked to "the dangerous manifestations of covert or even overt 
support for fascism" by Miroslav Grebenicek today. 
  In his statement given to CTK, Grebenicek, chairman of the 
Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia (KSCM), said that the way 
in which Benes was being attacked and scandalized "is too 
reminiscent of the rhetoric of Adolf Hitler and Czech 
collaborators (with fascism)." "We reject resolutely any 
challenging of the results of World War Two because similar 
steps would be not only an offense to the millions of victims of 
fascism, but a dangerous step leading to the destabilization of 
the whole of Europe as well," the statement says. 
  It warns that he who "supports the attacks (against the 
Benes 
decrees) threatens our national identity and opens up the road 
towards unlimited property restitution which would lead to the 
total collapse of not only the economy, but all social life in 
the Czech Republic." 
  Under the decrees, some 2.5 [million] Sudeten Germans were 
expelled from Czechoslovakia and their property was confiscated. 
The Sudeten German Landsmannschaft has now been claiming the 
property and the recognition of the right to homeland. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

