<H3> <TI>   Official Final Results of Elections Declared </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Final Results of Elections Declared </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1706092894 Budapest MTI in English 1925 GMT 16 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1706092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 16 Jun (MTI) -- The National Election 
Committee (NEC) has declared the official final results of the 
first and second rounds of the general elections, after the 
Supreme Court approved its decision on modifying the results in 
the sixth constituency -- Gyor-Moson-Sopron County (W Hungary) 
-- where Gyorgy Rasko (HDF) finished in first place after the 
re-count, instead of Gyula Varga (AFD). Thus, the Hungarian 
Democratic Forum receives one more seat (bringing the total to 
38) in Hungary's 386-seat National Assembly, while the Alliance 
of Free Democrats has one seat less (total: 69). 

</TEXT>

