<H3> <TI>   Status as WEU Observer `Unsatisfactory' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Status as WEU Observer `Unsatisfactory' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606214994 Warsaw PAP in English 2122 GMT 16 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1606214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, June 16 -- The permanent observer status 
given to Poland by the Parliamentary Assembly of the Western 
European Union (WEU) is unsatisfactory, head of the delegation 
of the Polish Parliament for spring session of the WEU assembly 
Deputy Longin Pastusiak said upon his arrival from a WEU session 
in Paris. The present status makes it impossible for the Polish 
delegation to cast votes, participate in committees' work and 
forward amendments to reports. 
  Speaking to journalists Pastusiak said that Poland's full 
integration with WEU, which under the Maastricht Treaty is to 
become an armed organization of the European Union, remains one 
of the priorities of the Polish policy. In his opinion, odds 
are that efforts of Polish delegation to attain this goal will 
bring results during the December session of the WEU 
Parliamentary Assembly. 

</TEXT>

