<H3> <TI>   Nigerian Ministries Trying To `Launder' Money </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nigerian Ministries Trying To `Launder' Money </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606211794 Warsaw PAP in English 2129 GMT 15 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1606211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gdansk, June 15 -- Several customers of a bank in 
the Gdansk province have been approached recently by Nigerian 
institutions and asked to agree to have big money transferred on 
their accounts. In return the Nigerians offered 30 percent of 
the transferred amount, a bank staffer told PAP on Wednesday. 
The bank customers rejected the Nigerian proposal and notified 
the bank whose authorities believe the Nigerians were trying to 
launder money in Poland. The Nigerians wanted to transfer many 
million dollars to each account. 
  The proposals came from the Nigerian Federal Ministry of 
Industry and Trade and the Federal Ministry of National Defence. 
The Nigerians justified their proposal with the unstable 
situation in their country and asked to keep the operation in 
secret. 
  A similar proposal was reported on Wednesday by the 
"DZIENNIK 
BALTYCKI" daily which wrote that the Nigerian Construction 
Ministry and the Nigerian national oil corporation wanted to 
transfer 57 million U.S. dollars. They wanted to pay 17.8 
million U.S. dollars for the transaction and sacrificed further 
4.2 million dollars for the servicing costs, read: bribes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

