<H3> <TI>   Official Supports Negotiations on Union Claims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Supports Negotiations on Union Claims </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606100094 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1819 GMT 15 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1606100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 15/6/1994 -- "Big trade union 
confederations -- Alfa Cartel especially -- gave us notice about 
a lot of union actions to be developed on June 14-21," said 
Octavian Partenie, secretary of state, head of the Government's 
Office for relations with trade unions and employers' 
organizations. 
  Referring to the union claims and the dialogue of government 
and unions, Octavian Partenie said "that their claims reached us 
through media." He added that "many of the claims are already 
settled or in the process of settlement, some are to be 
negotiated as they can not be settled on the spot and other ones 
cannot be even discussed." In the unrealistic claims ranking, 
the official mentioned a 50 per cent salary increase, a claim 
which means that "if we proceed to a 50 per cent salary rise 
today, we will have tomorrow a 60 per cent price increase and 
followed by a new salary increase, unemployment increase rate 
and a population increase rate who cannot live a decent 
life...and again a spiralling inflation." 
  At the end of his interview, Octavian Partenie expressed his 
confidence in a reciprocal wish for dialogue. "Only in a 
receptive and responsible dialogue can we find the proper 
solutions," he underlined, noticing that at the present stage 
unions should look towards the employers' organizations. "It is 
with the employers' organizations that they are conducting talks 
now and so it will be in the future too," said the Romanian 
official. 

</TEXT>

