  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 16/6/1994 -- The Romanian 
parliamentary delegation, headed by Adrian Nastase, speaker of 
the Chamber of Deputies, returned on 15 June from an official 
three-day visit to the Czech Republic. On arrival at Otopeni 
Airport, Speaker Nastase told the press that the Prague visit 
was a "success." "We have felt there much warmth and a great 
readiness for revigorating the political, economic and cultural 
relations between the two countries." 
  Also, Adrian Nastase assessed as "encouraging" the messages 
