<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks With PRC Official Focus on UN, Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks With PRC Official Focus on UN, Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606194894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1544 GMT 16 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1606194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 16/6/1994 -- Romanian-Chinese 
consultations at deputy minister level ended in Bucharest on 16 
June. The two delegations, headed by Qin Huasun, deputy foreign 
minister, and Ion Gorita, secretary of state, approached matters 
of multilateral diplomacy and especially problems on the UN 
agenda. 
  The visit to be paid here at the beginning of July by Li 
Peng, president of the Council of State of the People's Republic 
of China, the first at this level after 1990 paid by a Chinese 
official to Central and Eastern Europe, was also discussed by 
the two deputy ministers. 
  Regarding the multilateral diplomacy, the two delegations 
referred to such topics as the UN's reform and restructuring, 
especially concerning the Security Council, the peace-keeping 
operations, regional conflicts, with stress on developments in 
ex-Yugoslavia, human rights, and disarmament. Both parties 
expressed their "concern" in connection with the recent 
developments in the Korean peninsula and stressed that what was 
needed was "a political settlement negotiated among all parties 
concerned." 
  The representatives of the Chinese and Romanian foreign 
ministers noted pursuant to the consultations the existence of 
an "identity" of standpoints between the two countries 
concerning the major issues of concern to the UN. It was agreed 
that, based on the fine relations of cooperation, such kind of 
consultations should be continued, in view of establishing 
common modalities of action for the future UN session (September 
1994.) 

</TEXT>

