<H3> <TI>   Daily: Meciar Has Private `Intelligence Agency' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily: Meciar Has Private `Intelligence Agency' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1706104894 Prague CTK in English 1010 GMT 17 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1706104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kosice, East Slovakia June 17 (CTK) -- "Vladimir 
Meciar as Slovak premier ordered the Interior Ministry to watch 
head of its secretariat Anna Nagyova at the time when there was 
a minor misunderstanding between them," Ludovit Cernak, 
parliament deputy chairman and chairman of the National 
Democratic Party (NDS) confirms in the daily SLOVENSKY VYCHOD 
today. 
  Asked by the daily, Cernak confirmed the existence of a 
private firm which acts as information and intelligence agency 
for ex-Premier Meciar. The firm, according to SLOVENSKY VYCHOD, 
obtained "unofficial" information about Slovak high-ranking 
politicians. The paper says that Jaroslav Svechota, former 
Slovak interior minister in 1990 when Meciar led the ministry, 
works in the firm. 
  Cernak says that he has documents to prove that Meciar, in 
the interests of his Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), 
corrupted the Slovak National Party (SNS) when Cernak was its 
chairman, and had thus contributed to the victory of 
non-tolerant and radical wing. 

</TEXT>

