<H3> <TI>   Resettlement of Serbs in Podujeve Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Resettlement of Serbs in Podujeve Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606165694 Tirana ATA in English 1023 GMT 16 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1606165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, June 16 (ATA) -- During the day, 1,000 
Serbians are added to the population of Podujeve, a Kosova town 
98 percent of whose population are Albanians. 
  More than 1,000 Serbian workers and students are brought 
every day from the Serbia's town of Kursumlija and its suburbs 
in an organized way, by the expenses of the Serbian Communal 
Assembly. In evening they are taken to their homes. During the 
night, only the Serbian police and few Serbians. [sentence as 
received] The Serbian chairman of the Podujeve Communal 
Assembly told the BORBA newspaper that the Serbians make up 1.6 
percent of the total population while there are Albanians are 
120,000. 

