<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Plans 20-Percent Cut in Territorial Units </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Plans 20-Percent Cut in Territorial Units </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1906120694 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI in Romanian 9 Jun 
94 p 10 </F>

<F P=103> AU1906120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Doru Dragomir] </F>
  [Text] On 13-16 June the major territorial commands of the 
Ministry of National Defense will organize the second stage of 
testing personnel in these military units. On the basis of 
certain regulations of the Defense Ministry, the personnel in 
the military commands will have to take a number of exams. 
These exams are organized directly by the General Staff and are 
part of the process of transforming and restructuring the Army. 
  In accordance with the importance, area, and size of the 
commands, it is possible that the number of personnel will be 
cut by a maximum of 15 percent. The first stage of testing 
personnel took place in the second half of May at a local level. 
At the level of the entire ministry, a maximum 20-percent cut 
in personnel is envisaged in territorial and central structures. 
The most important territorial commands of the Ministry of 
National Defense are in Bucharest, Bacau, Cluj, and Drobeta 
Turnu Severin. 

</TEXT>

