<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Preliminary Local Government Election Results </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Preliminary Local Government Election Results </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006073494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0700 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006073494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the initial and still incomplete 
results of the self-government elections held yesterday, the 
Democratic Left Alliance [SLD] has won in Bedzin, Bydgoszcz, 
Czestochowa, Kielce, Konin, Koszalin, Legnica, Lodz, Olsztyn, 
Plock, Suwalki, Walbrzych, and Wloclawek. 
  In Lublin, almost the same number of votes was received by 
candidates of the SLD, the center-right, and the Freedom Union 
[UW]. 
  In Warsaw, victory went to a coalition of Freedom Union, the 
Conservative Party, and the Peasant-Christian Party; in Gdansk, 
Gdynia, Krakow, and Wroclaw to the Freedom Union. The 
center-right received the greatest number of votes in Bialystok, 
Chorzow, Lomza, Przemysl, Rzeszow, and Torun. 
  The turnout was low--between 25 and 40 percent. The official 
results of the self-government elections should be known on 
Friday, State Electoral Commission Secretary Kazimierz Czaplicki 
told this station today. 

</TEXT>

