<H3> <TI>   Strike at Katowice Steelworks Suspended </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Strike at Katowice Steelworks Suspended </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806080094 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0635 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Katowice, 18 Jun--The strike at Katowice Steelworks, 
which has been in effect since 1 June, was suspended this 
morning. The suspension will be in force until all demands are 
met and a new pay agreement coordinated, Mariusz Kwasniowski, of 
the steelworks' information office, reports. 
  He added that as agreed between the strike committee and the 
management, each worker will get a pay raise of 1.5 million 
zlotys gross per month, with effect from 1 May. 

