<H3> <TI>   Strikers at Warsaw Steelworks Begin Sit-In </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Strikers at Warsaw Steelworks Begin Sit-In </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806083594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0800 
GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1806083594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A sit-in began this morning at the board offices of 
the Lucchini Steelworks in Warsaw. Jacek Gasiorowski, 
cochairman of the Solidarity strike committee, said this form of 
protest will last until the board begins negotiations with the 
strikers. 
  The dispute at the Lucchini-Warszawa Steelworks began on 9 
June. The steelworkers are demanding a pay raise of 30 percent 
and that modernization of the steelworks be undertaken by the 
Italian owner. The strike has been organized jointly by 
Solidarity and the National Trade Union Alliance [OPZZ]. 

