<H3> <TI>   B-H, HVO Leaders View Washington Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    B-H, HVO Leaders View Washington Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1706155594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1706155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commanders of the 1st, 3d, and 7th Corps of the 
Army of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina -- Vahid Karavelic, 
Sakib Mahmuljin, and Mehmed Alagic -- met with Vitez Region 
Commander Filip Filipovic at a command of the Army of the 
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina today. They met to discuss the 
concretization of the military part of the agreement signed in 
Washington. In an atmosphere of complete mutual understanding, 
representatives of the Army of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the Croatian Defense Council [HVO] 
expressed interest in implementing the details regarding the 
formation of the joint Federal Army. 
  The effects of the truce signed between the Army of the 
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina and the HVO on 25 February 1994 
that have been achieved so far represent a good-quality basis 
for realizing tasks issued by the Joint Command, and the regions 
covered by the 1st, 3d, and 7th Corps, as well as the Vitez 
Region are definitely important for their implementation in the 
field. On this occasion, attention was also focused on the 
joint activity of the forces of the Army of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the HVO in the struggle against chetniks. 
The commanders assessed that the talks today were extremely 
successful. 

</TEXT>

