<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Aggressor' Steps Up Brcko Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Aggressor' Steps Up Brcko Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2006093194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2006093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hamiz Deronjic from Brcko] </F>
  [Text] The intensity of the Serbian aggressor's combat 
activities escalated on the Brcko battlefield last night. 
Sporadically but persistently throughout the night, the enemy 
used 60-mm mortars, antiaircraft machine guns, antiaircraft 
guns, and rifles to attack the defense positions of Brcko. The 
defense positions in Djukici, in the central part of the 
battlefield, and in Vranovaca were targeted the most frequently. 
  An enemy saboteur group was chased away in the region of 
Boderiste at approximately 2000 last night, and at 2200 the 
defenders repeated their success in thwarting an attempt by 
chetnik saboteurs to penetrate into the Vranovaca area. 
  The aggressor continues to encounter major difficulties 
mobilizing soldiers. Intelligence information suggests that, 
over the past month and a half, the Serbian aggressor has 
carried out a whole series of raids in Bijeljina and in nearby 
villages. The chetnik military police are rounding up potential 
military conscripts in apartments, on the streets, bus stops, 
and even in hospitals, regardless of their (?rank), profession, 
or health condition, to transport them to special training camps. 
  However, not even this latest aspect of mobilization has 
provided much of a chance for success for the aggressor. As 
soon as they arrive on the front, these forcefully mobilized 
soldiers of the so-called Srpska republic army desert the front 
lines in the Bosnian Sava Basin and Mt. Majevica at the first 
given opportunity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

