<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Suffer `Huge Losses' in Vozuca Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Suffer `Huge Losses' in Vozuca Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906113094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1906113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There has been no let-up in chetnik attacks on the 
battlefields in the Third Corps' operational zone. They 
launched fierce attacks yesterday, especially on the Mount Ozren 
and Vozuca battlefields, using all types of heavy artillery. 
Here is a report from the Third Corps press center: 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Dozens of shells hit 
Hajdarevici, (Brasnevine), Livade, and Kamenica, and hundreds of 
large caliber shells were fired on the defense lines along the 
entire front line. The Third Corps responded to these attacks, 
so the fighting around Vozuca raged all day yesterday. In 
addition to frenzied artillery attacks, the chetniks launched 
several unsuccessful infantry attacks in which they suffered the 
largest losses so far. We estimate that several dozen of the 
aggressor's dead soldiers remained in the no-man's-land between 
the front lines. Many of their wounded were abandoned during the 
disorderly retreat. The huge losses incurred by the chetniks 
during their attempts to capture strategic locations around 
Zavidovici, the aim of their offensive, are the reason for the 
daily calls for reinforcements. 
  In addition to the attacks on the Vozuca front, chetniks 
were 
also active on the Celic battlefield, where they stepped up 
provocations and occasionally opened fire from 82-mm mortars. 
The situation was similar in the Tesanj area, the free 
territories around Teslic, and Doboj, where the aggressor used 
infantry weapons and a (?D-1) tank to shell Kalosevici. 

</TEXT>

