<H3> <TI>   `Mass Exodus' of Doboj Serbs as Muslims Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Mass Exodus' of Doboj Serbs as Muslims Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906200394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1900 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1906200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Doboj, 19 Jun (TANJUG) -- Muslim units have 
resumed attacks on Serb positions and residential areas along 
all frontlines in the Doboj region, the information service of 
the Srpska republic army's 1st Krajina Corps said this evening. 
[passage omitted] For the fifth day running, strong Muslim 
forces, reinforced by units from Zenica and Kakanj, are 
attacking Serb positions and villages along the Ozren-Vozuca 
front. The attacks are focused on the area between the Krivaja 
river and the southwestern part of the Ozren-Vozuca front where, 
with strong artillery and tank support, the Muslim forces are 
launching infantry attacks and using terrorist-sabotage groups 
in attempts to break through Serb lines and destroy all Serb 
villages. This is why a mass exodus of the Serb population has 
begun. 
  According to the statement, the Muslims are also attacking 
Serb defense lines in Vozuca from the direction of Banovici, 
Lukavac, Zivinice, and Tuzla. According to the statement, it is 
becoming more obvious that the UN Protection Force has been 
offering logistical and fire support in the area between Ribnica 
and Vijenac. A mass exodus of the population has also begun from 
this area after many civilians, mostly children and women, were 
killed in Muslim artillery attacks on their villages. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

