<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Inter-Muslim Clashes Resume in Western Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Inter-Muslim Clashes Resume in Western Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706150294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1350 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Petrovac, 17 June (TANJUG) -- The offensive launched 
by pro-Izetbegovic forces against positions held by Fikret 
Abdic's units in Cazin Krajina in northern part of the Bihac 
region has continued for the seventh day in a row, local Muslim 
media reports. 
  According to the same sources, last night remnants of the 
5th 
Corps of the so-called Bosnia-Herzegovina army launched an 
infantry and mortar attack against positions and residential 
areas controlled by the army of the Autonomous Province of 
Western Bosnia [APWB] from the direction of Djogici and 
Pajezitovici. The Abdic proautonomy forces repelled the attack 
without suffering any losses. 
  Alija Izetbegovic's forces resumed the attacks this morning 
from the direction of Zeljkovici, Porcici, Memici, and Liskovac. 
Later in the day fighting also took place in the Beganovici, 
Todorovo, and Pecigrad areas. 
  Local media in the Bihac region, loyal to Alija Izetbegovic, 
report that 5th Corps forces have been inflicting heavy losses 
on the army of the APWB and that both sides have suffered 
casualties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-32064 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu118_i_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-118 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  19 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting in Cazin Krajina Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting in Cazin Krajina Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1906135594 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1906135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fierce inter-Muslim fighting is taking place in the 
Cazin Krajina. The forces of the Autonomous Province of Western 
Bosnia last night fired a number artillery projectiles at the 
positions of the 5th Corps of the Muslim army loyal to the 
government in Sarajevo. This was reported by Muslim radio in 
Sarajevo this morning. Eight soldiers of the 5th Corps were 
killed and 12 seriously wounded. 
  ZBIA Information Agency this morning reported on significant 
military successes by the advocates of autonomy, who, as 
claimed, have pushed out Izetbegovic's faction from a 
significant part of the former Cazin commune. 

</TEXT>

