<H3> <TI>   Economics Minister Holds Talks in Baghdad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economics Minister Holds Talks in Baghdad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906173894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1520 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1906173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 19 Jun (TANJUG) -- A Yugoslav delegation, 
headed by Milorad Unkovic, federal minister for economic 
relations with foreign countries and president of the group for 
economic and technical cooperation within a joint Yugoslav-Iraqi 
committee, held talks in Baghdad today with Iraqi Deputy Prime 
Minister Tariq 'Aziz. 
  During the talks, described as cordial, both sides expressed 
satisfaction over the cooperation between their countries so 
far, and prospects to promote it further when conditions make 
this possible. Global world problems after the end of the Cold 
War and its implications on the two countries were also 
discussed. 
  Milorad Unkovic briefed Tariq 'Aziz about the current 
political situation in Yugoslavia and the economic recovery 
program. He also explained to his host the position of the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia on the former Bosnia-Herzegovina 
and other war-torn parts of the former Yugoslavia. The Yugoslav 
minister stressed that Yugoslavia should be reintegrated in the 
international community as soon as possible. 
  The Iraqi deputy prime minister said that the parties in the 
conflict should show more flexibility in the talks in order to 
find a compromise solution leading to a lasting peace. 
  Radoslav Bulajic, deputy Yugoslav foreign minister, briefed 
Tariq 'Aziz on the international position of the FRY [Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia] and its foreign policy principles. The 
main direction of Yugoslavia's policy is that of peace, of 
resolving all conflicts peacefully and observing all 
international norms and the UN Charter, Bulajic stressed. The 
talks resume in Baghdad tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-32070 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu118_y_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
