<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Identical Attitudes With Serbian </F>
Socialists"] 
  [Text] The press conference of the Democratic Christian 
Party in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- 
FYROM], held in Belgrade, focused on the Orthodox religion and 
Macedonia. Representatives of this party have been guests of the 
ruling Socialist Party in Serbia [SPS] for already two days. We 
are discussing possibilities of opening a process of unity of 
all orthodox and Christian peoples in the Balkans, as a part of 
the all-European integration process, the party leader Vasil 
Ristevski said. He stressed his party has identical points of 
view with the Serbian Socialists on all main issues concerning 
the Balkan political crises. He also pointed out he had been 
assured Macedonia is not faced with any danger coming from its 
northern brotherly neighbor. 
