<H3> <TI>   Party Protests `Violation' of Serbian Rights </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Party Protests `Violation' of Serbian Rights </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1706135694 Skopje NOVA MAKEDONIJA in Macedonian 14 Jun 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> AU1706135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje NOVA MAKEDONIJA </F>
<F P=105>  Macedonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Party of Yugoslavs in Macedonia 
[DPJM] has protested after the Macedonian authorities banned the 
entry and stay in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] of some Serbian Orthodox priests, and 
considers that this cannot be compatible with a democratic 
society. 
  The DPJM has also protested because yesterday some other 
Serbian Orthodox priests were not allowed to enter Macedonia as 
civilians either, which represents a serious violation of the 
democratic and constitutional principles of Macedonia, and it is 
another instance of the tough repression of the population of 
Serbian nationality, which has already been deprived of its 
rights. 
  The DPMJ has also protested the irrational and, in its view, 
irresponsible statements by the Head of the Macedonian Orthodox 
Church Mihail. 

</TEXT>

