<H3> <TI>   Clash in Tetovo Over Census; One Stabbed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Clash in Tetovo Over Census; One Stabbed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2006090794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2006090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Macedonian youth was stabbed during the clashes 
between Macedonians and members of the Albanian ethnic minority 
in Tetovo. The tension between the two ethnic communities is 
rising in light of the upcoming public census in Macedonia [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM]. 
  The Albanians, who officially constitute 23 percent of the 
population, boycotted the last census in 1991. They claim they 
account for 40 percent of Macedonia's population. In western 
Macedonia, which is seen as a potential hotbed of clashes, the 
Albanians make up approximately 70 percent of the population. 

</TEXT>

