<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] Abdic's forces have continued to use long-range 
artillery from well inside the occupied territory of Velika 
Kladusa, with continuing support by the chetniks from the 
so-called Serbian autonomous region of Krajina. The intensity 
of the shelling with tanks, howitzers, and mortars is best 
illustrated by the fact that over the last two days from [words 
indistinct] they have fired over 6,000 shells, razing [word 
indistinct] villages to the ground. There have been many 
casualties. 
  Since midday, the members of the Kladusa paramilitary have 
intensified their attacks along the entire front line, and 
reliable reports claim that Abdic's (?fascist) headquarters is 
preparing a new offensive and new attacks to recapture lost 
ground. However, he still has problems with forceful 
mobilization, and with generally mobilization, since the 
population is simply rejecting all calls. It is important to 
stress that the population's cooperation is [word indistinct] 
every day. 

</TEXT>

