<F P=106> [Report by Hamiz Deronjic from Brcko] </F>
  [Text] Regarding the Brcko front, the latest cease-fire 
agreement will only remain a piece of paper. Not for one single 
day has the enemy halted combat activities on the Brcko front. 
Over the last few evenings he has even intensified them. This 
was the case last night. 
  Early in the evening, our fighters resisted several attacks 
by Chetnik surveillance-saboteur groups in the central part of 
the front. Along with intensified provocations [word 
indistinct] antiaircraft machine guns, and antiaircraft guns 
along the entire front of the Brcko battlefield the Serbian 
aggressor between 2000 and 2200 hours last night on several 
occasions from mortars [words indistinct] the positions of 
defenders and the civilian settlements in the Boderiste are, one 
can easily say, a constant target of the enemy artillery. 
[Words indistinct] that the Serbian aggressor on this as well 
as on all previous [words indistinct] on the Brcko front is 
using to prepare new attacks on free Brcko territory. In this 
way in the last 24 hours intense enemy activities [words 
indistinct]. On two occasions last night -- first at 1800 and 
then 2100 -- we registered the arrival of large convoys of enemy 
trucks and combat vehicles from the direction of Rasevi and 
Potocari in the temporarily occupied Brcko. The fighters of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army and the Croatian Defense Council on the 
Brcko front are carefully monitoring the aggressor's every step, 
[words indistinct] not to allow him to [words indistinct] the 
free Brcko territory. 

</TEXT>

