  [Text] Czech Deputy Finance Minister Vladimir Rudlovcak has 
signed a Czech-Russian intergovernmental agreement in Moscow. 
The agreement concerns the Russian debt to the Czech Republic 
in the amount of $3.5 billion that Russia should repay by 2003. 
The Czech Republic will receive $52 million this year, $101 
million next year, and $301.9 million in 1996. 

