<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sees Sofia `Conspiracy' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sees Sofia `Conspiracy' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2006102794 Sofia KONTINENT in Bulgarian 16 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2006102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia KONTINENT </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Skopje -- Ljubomir Frckovski, minister of internal 
affairs of the Republic of Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia--FYROM], told correspondents that 
Macedonian politicians had held a meeting in the Rila Hotel in 
Sofia with leaders of the Internal Macedonian Revolutionary 
Organization-Union of Macedonian Societies [VMRO-SMD]. They 
allegedly agreed with them a plan of action during the period 
preceding the parliamentary elections in Macedonia. It was 
claimed that three groups were set up, to deal with ideological, 
propaganda, and military matters, in which the Rakovski Officers 
Legion was also reportedly involved. The plans of the 
"conspiracy" included setting up a radio transmitter in the 
vicinity of the Macedonian border. On the other side of the 
border, within Macedonia itself, the "groups" were supposedly 
intending to work to overcome the differences between parties 
whose stances were close to one another. 

</TEXT>

